Wayne


On Tue, Apr 14, 2026 at 4:21=E2=80=AFAM Andrew Gunn ( Compass Garden Machin=
ery) <
andrew.gunn@compassgm.co.uk> wrote:

> Hi Guys.
>
> I had a visit with the factory that makes the cordless range yesterday.
> As you know they have heavily invested in us to push this project.
>
> Overall the meeting was positive but he was a little critical of the way
> we are presenting the range on line.
>
>
>    1. He thinks all tools should be available as a complete machine.  So
>    for example the lawnmower with battery/s and charger - one price
>    2. Also to offer tool only
>    3. More life style images in the description
>    4. Larger story about each product on the website
>    5. He picked on the lawnmower - he said not clear need to buy two
>    batteries and he said in bundle not clear what two batteries are as an=
 item
>    and that you need them.
>    6. Showing the one battery fits all the tools. - he wants the battery
>    in the market in mass as this is where the growth is.
>
>
> In defence we said that the websites in current form would not allow us t=
o
> do this and manage the stocks without development.
>
> Answer was well develop the answer quickly given the investment.
>
> He feels each day we are missing opportunity especially in the mass
> channel, and the websites with the high spec lawnmower we have.
>
> Can we look at how to achieve this on all channels asap - make the stock
> control work properly and cost etc for what we need to do.
>
> At the end of the day Lenny will have up to =C2=A31m on the line with us =
so we
> owe it to him to get this right.
>
> Also - cash wise we have around 3 months to get this moved.
>
> Given the shortage of petrol lawnmowers for a few weeks this should be lo=
w
> hanging fruit for us.
>
> Appreciate feed back asap
>
> Thx
>
> Andrew
>
>
>
> Sent from Outlook for Mac
>

